== Events == * {{ill|Ninna|ja|仁和|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 3rd year（[[Julian calendar]] [[887]] [[December 9]]） – The Daijō-daijin and Fujiwara Mototsune were appointed as {{ill|Kanpaku|ja|関白|fr|Kanpaku|ru|Кампаку|sv|Kampaku|uk|Кампаку|zh|關白|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, becoming the first commoner Kanpaku. * {{ill|Tenkei|ja|天慶|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 2nd year ([[Julian calendar]] [[940]] [[January 3]]） – Taira no Masakado attacked the Hitachi provincial government, seizing official seals and capturing Hitachi-no-kasuke and Fujiwara Noriaki. * [[承徳]] 1st year ([[Julian calendar]] [[1097]] [[December 27]]） – Due to a celestial event, the era name was changed from Eichō to Shōtoku. * [[乾元 (日本)|乾元]] 1st year ([[Julian calendar]] [[1302]] [[December 10]]） – The era name was changed from Seian to Kangen for the accession of Emperor Go-Nijō. * [[安永]] 8th year（[[Gregorian calendar]] [[1779]] [[December 28]]） – Hiraga Gennai was imprisoned on suspicion of accidentally killing two of his disciples. * {{ill|Genji|ja|元治|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1864]] [[December 19]]） – The Tokugawa shogunate signed the "Yokohama Residence Memorandum" with Britain, the United States, France, and the Netherlands.
== Births == * [[En'ō]] 1st year ([[Julian calendar]] [[1239]] [[December 17]]） – Fujiwara Yoritsugu, the 5th shogun of the Kamakura shogunate (d. [[1256]]). * {{ill|Kyōhō|ja|享保|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 18th year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1733]] [[December 26]]） – Makino Sadanaga, a politician (d. [[1796]]). * {{ill|Enkyō|ja|Enkyō|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 4th year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1747]] [[December 17]]） – Arakida Hisao, a kokugaku scholar (d. [[1804]]). * {{ill|Bunkyū|ja|文久|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 3rd year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1863]] [[December 31]]） – Nagase Tomorō, the founder of Kao (d. [[1911]]). * [[Meiji era|Meiji]] 3rd year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1871]] [[January 11]]） – Taoka Reiun, a writer and critic (d. [[1912]]).
== Deaths == * [[Bunmei]] 13th year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1481]] [[December 12]]） – Ikkyū Sōjun, a Zen monk (born [[1394]]). * {{ill|Man'en|ja|万延|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1861]] [[January 1]]） – Asaka Gensai, a Confucian scholar ({{ill|Ru (Confucian scholar)|ja|儒学者|zh|儒生|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) (born [[1791]]).
