{{Lunisolar November|qq=}}
'''November 21''' is the 21st day of the month {{ill|November (Lunisolar)|ja|11月 (旧暦)|lt=November (Shimotsuki)|qq=}}, the 11th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=}} day is {{ill|Senshō|ja|先勝|qq=}}.

== Events ==
* {{ill|Ninna|ja|仁和|qq=}} 3rd year（[[Julian calendar]]  [[887]] [[December 9]]） – The Daijō-daijin and Fujiwara Mototsune were appointed as {{ill|Kanpaku|ja|関白|fr|Kanpaku|ru|Кампаку|sv|Kampaku|uk|Кампаку|zh|關白|qq=}}, becoming the first commoner Kanpaku.
* {{ill|Tenkei|ja|天慶|qq=}} 2nd year ([[Julian calendar]]   [[940]] [[January 3]]） – Taira no Masakado attacked the Hitachi provincial government, seizing official seals and capturing Hitachi-no-kasuke and Fujiwara Noriaki.
* [[承徳]] 1st year ([[Julian calendar]]   [[1097]] [[December 27]]） – Due to a celestial event, the era name was changed from Eichō to Shōtoku.
* [[乾元 (日本)|乾元]] 1st year ([[Julian calendar]]   [[1302]] [[December 10]]） – The era name was changed from Seian to Kangen for the accession of Emperor Go-Nijō.
* [[安永]] 8th year（[[Gregorian calendar]]  [[1779]] [[December 28]]） – Hiraga Gennai was imprisoned on suspicion of accidentally killing two of his disciples.
* {{ill|Genji|ja|元治|qq=}} 1st year ([[Gregorian calendar]]   [[1864]] [[December 19]]） – The Tokugawa shogunate signed the "Yokohama Residence Memorandum" with Britain, the United States, France, and the Netherlands.

== Births ==
* [[En'ō]] 1st year ([[Julian calendar]]   [[1239]] [[December 17]]） – Fujiwara Yoritsugu, the 5th shogun of the Kamakura shogunate (d. [[1256]]).
* {{ill|Kyōhō|ja|享保|qq=}} 18th year ([[Gregorian calendar]]   [[1733]] [[December 26]]） – Makino Sadanaga, a politician (d. [[1796]]).
* {{ill|Enkyō|ja|Enkyō|qq=}} 4th year ([[Gregorian calendar]]   [[1747]] [[December 17]]） – Arakida Hisao, a kokugaku scholar (d. [[1804]]).
* {{ill|Bunkyū|ja|文久|qq=}} 3rd year ([[Gregorian calendar]]   [[1863]] [[December 31]]） – Nagase Tomorō, the founder of Kao (d. [[1911]]).
* [[Meiji era|Meiji]] 3rd year ([[Gregorian calendar]]   [[1871]] [[January 11]]） – Taoka Reiun, a writer and critic (d. [[1912]]).

== Deaths ==
* [[Bunmei]] 13th year ([[Gregorian calendar]]   [[1481]] [[December 12]]） – Ikkyū Sōjun, a Zen monk (born [[1394]]).
* {{ill|Man'en|ja|万延|qq=}} 1st year ([[Gregorian calendar]]   [[1861]] [[January 1]]） – Asaka Gensai, a Confucian scholar ({{ill|Ru (Confucian scholar)|ja|儒学者|zh|儒生|qq=}}) (born [[1791]]).

