== Births == * [[En'ō]] 1st year ([[Julian calendar]] [[1239]] [[December 17]]） – Fujiwara Yoritsugu, the 5th shogun of the Kamakura shogunate (d. [[1256]]). * [[:en:Kyōhō|Kyōhō]] 18th year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1733]] [[December 26]]） – Makino Sadanaga, a politician (d. [[1796]]). * {{ill|Enkyō|ja|Enkyō|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Enkyō|qq=}} 4th year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1747]] [[December 17]]） – Arakida Hisao, a kokugaku scholar (d. [[1804]]). * [[:en:Bunkyū|Bunkyū]] 3rd year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1863]] [[December 31]]） – Nagase Tomorō, the founder of Kao (d. [[1911]]). * [[Meiji era|Meiji]] 3rd year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1871]] [[January 11]]） – Taoka Reiun, a writer and critic (d. [[1912]]).
== Deaths == * [[Bunmei]] 13th year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1481]] [[December 12]]） – Ikkyū Sōjun, a Zen monk (born [[1394]]). * [[:en:Man'en|Man'en]] 1st year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1861]] [[January 1]]） – Asaka Gensai, a Confucian scholar ({{ill|Ru (Confucian scholar)|ja|儒学者|zh|儒生|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ru (Confucian scholar)|qq=}}) (born [[1791]]).
