== Events == * [[:en:Ninna|Ninna]] 3rd year（[[Julian calendar]] [[887]] [[December 9]]） – The Daijō-daijin and Fujiwara Mototsune were appointed as {{ill|Kanpaku|ja|関白|fr|Kanpaku|ru|Кампаку|sv|Kampaku|uk|Кампаку|zh|關白|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kanpaku|qq=}}, becoming the first commoner Kanpaku. * [[:en:Tengyō|Tenkei]] 2nd year ([[Julian calendar]] [[940]] [[January 3]]） – Taira no Masakado attacked the Hitachi provincial government, seizing official seals and capturing Hitachi-no-kasuke and Fujiwara Noriaki. * [[承徳]] 1st year ([[Julian calendar]] [[:en:1097|1097]] [[December 27]]） – Due to a celestial event, the era name was changed from Eichō to Shōtoku. * [[乾元 (日本)|乾元]] 1st year ([[Julian calendar]] [[:en:1302|1302]] [[December 10]]） – The era name was changed from Seian to Kangen for the accession of Emperor Go-Nijō. * [[安永]] 8th year（[[Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1779|1779]] [[December 28]]） – Hiraga Gennai was imprisoned on suspicion of accidentally killing two of his disciples. * [[:en:Genji era|Genji]] 1st year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1864|1864]] [[December 19]]） – The Tokugawa shogunate signed the "Yokohama Residence Memorandum" with Britain, the United States, France, and the Netherlands.
== Births == * [[En'ō]] 1st year ([[Julian calendar]] [[:en:1239|1239]] [[December 17]]） – Fujiwara Yoritsugu, the 5th shogun of the Kamakura shogunate (d. [[:en:1256|1256]]). * [[:en:Kyōhō|Kyōhō]] 18th year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1733|1733]] [[December 26]]） – Makino Sadanaga, a politician (d. [[:en:1796|1796]]). * {{ill|Enkyō|ja|Enkyō|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Enkyō|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} 4th year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1747|1747]] [[December 17]]） – Arakida Hisao, a kokugaku scholar (d. [[:en:1804|1804]]). * [[:en:Bunkyū|Bunkyū]] 3rd year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1863|1863]] [[December 31]]） – Nagase Tomorō, the founder of Kao (d. [[1911]]). * [[Meiji era|Meiji]] 3rd year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1871|1871]] [[January 11]]） – Taoka Reiun, a writer and critic (d. [[1912]]).
== Deaths == * [[Bunmei]] 13th year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1481|1481]] [[December 12]]） – Ikkyū Sōjun, a Zen monk (born [[:en:1394|1394]]). * [[:en:Man'en|Man'en]] 1st year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1861|1861]] [[January 1]]） – Asaka Gensai, a Confucian scholar ({{ill|Ru (Confucian scholar)|ja|儒学者|zh|儒生|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ru (Confucian scholar)|qq=}}) (born [[:en:1791|1791]]).
